The article is a transcript of President Biden's speech at the SK Siltron CSS Facility in Bay City, Michigan. In his speech, President Biden thanks the Michigan governor and congressional leaders for their support and discusses the investments being made in American manufacturing, particularly in the semiconductor industry. He highlights the importance of bringing chip production back to the United States and reducing reliance on overseas manufacturing. President Biden also emphasizes the need to invest in clean energy and infrastructure, and the positive impact these investments will have on job creation and the economy. He concludes by expressing his optimism for America's future and the resilience of the United States.